## Verification

- node --check on all 4 modified js files — PASS
- Browser smoke test (port 3996, /wraithgrove):
  - WG.HuntPlayer.REPAIR_TUNABLES → { REPAIR_HOVER_DELAY: 3, REPAIR_RATE: 0.25, REPAIR_HP_PER_WOOD: 8, REPAIR_RANGE: 36 } ✓
  - All 47 WG modules load clean, no console errors
  - Synthetic end-to-end (force-built turret @ HP 30/80, player on top, 20 wood):
    - tick(2.95): HP unchanged (hover < threshold) ✓
    - tick(1.05) after threshold: HP=62 (+32 = 4 wood × 8 HP), wood=16, 4 repair:tick events ✓
    - tick more to fill: HP capped at 80, repair:complete fired once,
      audio:repair_complete fired once (forwarded by hunt-fx listener) ✓
    - Player walks out of range: repairHover=0, repairDrainTimer=0 (timers reset) ✓
- Console errors: zero from W-Building-Repair scope.

## Polish Mandate (Architect 2026-05-02)

- Hover ring eased growth: `1 - Math.pow(1 - t01, 3)` — ease-out cubic, fast initial
  growth that settles near 1.0 (read: "wind-up tension resolving").
- Wrench gentle bobble: `Math.sin(t * 5.5) * 1.6` px on Y during active repair
  (~5.5 rad/s = ~0.88 Hz, low amplitude — alive, not jittery).
- repair:complete trauma: 0.15 (between repair:tick silence and turret:destroyed 0.4 — small
  but felt punctuation for the heal payoff).
- Green burst: 12 particles, ring shape, life 0.70s, colors a8f0a0/80e088/fff0c0
  (green + warm cream tone — heal not poison).

## Out of scope (per worker brief)

- Campfire repair: not in scope (campfires don't have HP; only turrets do).
- "Repair 2× speed" ad-buff: tunables are NAMED constants ready for that hook;
  the buff itself is a future worker.
- Visual playtest gif: scheduled-task run cannot synthesize a real user gesture
  to dismiss "tap to begin" splash, so the in-game hover→drain→complete visual
  sequence was verified through (1) functional event-chain unit test in eval,
  (2) syntax check, (3) code inspection against drawCampfireRegenRings pattern.
  Manual playtest by the Architect: build a turret (or instant_turret buff),
  let an enemy damage it, walk within 36u, watch ring fill 3s → wrench appears
  → wood drains 0.25s/each, HP +8/wood until full (or wood out).

